com.autonomy.aci.client.transport.impl

Class AciHttpClientImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.autonomy.aci.client.transport.impl.AciHttpClientImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AciHttpClient
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GssAciHttpClientImpl

    public class AciHttpClientImpl
extends Object
implements AciHttpClient
    Implementation of the AciHttpClient interface that provides the actual HTTP communication mechanism. This implementation uses the HttpClient provided by the Apache HttpComponents project. It defaults to using the HTTP GET method, if you wish to send ACI actions with the HTTP POST method, then call the setUsePostMethod(boolean) method with true.

    This implementation of the AciHttpClient interface does no configuration of the HttpClient that it uses. It expects all the configuration to have been done by the user before passing it to this object. This configuration can be done in normal code, via the HttpClientFactory, or via an IoC container like Spring.

    See Also:
    Apache HttpComponents
